title: internal compiler error: encountered incremental compilation error with evaluate_obligation(81a04ba1514a6055-41c619c14401651b)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
<!--
Thank you for finding an Internal Compiler Error! 🧊  If possible, try to provide
a minimal verifiable example. You can read "Rust Bug Minimization Patterns" for
how to create smaller examples.
http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/
-->

Unfortunately I cannot share the code I was compiling. I have shared as much detail as I can below.

At the time, I was running cargo build, but I have the VSCode rust-analyzer extension running in the background at all times so that could have interacted with it somehow.

Once I did `cargo clean -p engine` as suggested, this fixed itself.


### Meta
<!--
If you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the
bug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.
-->

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
rustc 1.68.2 (9eb3afe9e 2023-03-27)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: 9eb3afe9ebe9c7d2b84b71002d44f4a0edac95e0
commit-date: 2023-03-27
host: x86_64-apple-darwin
release: 1.68.2
LLVM version: 15.0.6
```
Switched to nightly and this did compile fine:
```
giselleserate@C02F14VAMD6T engine-rs % rustc --version --verbose
rustc 1.70.0-nightly (5e1d3299a 2023-03-31)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: 5e1d3299a290026b85787bc9c7e72bcc53ac283f
commit-date: 2023-03-31
host: x86_64-apple-darwin
release: 1.70.0-nightly
LLVM version: 16.0.0
```
This is also able to compile on beta:
```
giselleserate@C02F14VAMD6T engine-rs % rustc --version --verbose
rustc 1.69.0-beta.6 (6a97551bc 2023-04-02)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: 6a97551bcbc982df3a2da1683611dc11dc1d40cc
commit-date: 2023-04-02
host: x86_64-apple-darwin
release: 1.69.0-beta.6
LLVM version: 15.0.7
```
